profile_positions.description:
Pursuit of my VIE Mission in Faurecia - Valencia, Spain

Development of a new module in the same app

Project: After having sucessfully delivered and deployed the new workspace, I was in charge of the development of a new module in the same app. My tasks were similar to my last project:
- Defined Users' need;
- Feasibility with developers;
- Wrote User Stories;
- User Acceptance Test phase (ATDD), Wrote and Executed Test Plan (BDD);
- Deployment to users;
- Procedure updating;
- Progress Reporting to the team.

I also kept working on the Launch workspace by supporting users in case of issues, providing usual training sessions and implementing improvements on their requests.

(a Mission VIE is a temporary contract of 2 years maximum, opened to young professional newly graduated (from 23 to 28 years old), which enables the candidate to work for a French company abroad)

Development of a web application workspace and IT support for Launch teams all around the world - IT
1st year in Czech Republic (Mlada Boleslav) and 2nd year in Spain (València)

Project: My main project was participating into the development of a workspace (Launch Book) for a PPM application. My main tasks were:
- Understood current work practises and processes (Visits to several plants in Poland, Slovakia and Czech Republic);
- Defined users' need (User Experience);
- Proposed solutions / mock ups to users;
- Checked technical feasibility with IT Tool manager and developers;
- Wrote and managed list of User Stories in order to implement them for the next development sprints;
- Prioritized User Stories;
- Tested solutions and created defects if needed (User Acceptance Test phase);
- Planned and provided training sessions to Launch users and updated training documents.

Results:
- 100% developed and deployed over 700 users, in 90 sites in the world;
- Reduction of the number of issues / tickets: from 3-4 tickets per day to 1-2 per week;
- More than 100 of improvements implemented.


Other activities:
- Participation into the development of other modules in the same Application: Process definition, mock ups, feasibility, tests and deployment;
- Solved VBA problems in Excel file which ensure the following of Launch KPI;
- Ensured data consistency for weekly reporting.

Skills: Communication (French, English (C1-C2) and Spanish (B2-C1)), Adaptability, Project Management, Continuous Improvement, Autonomy, Empathy, Problem Solving, VBA, International mindset, Flexibility, Team spirit

Process Optimization to meet the AS9100D requirements - Quality
Affected to the quality department and the AS9100D project team, I conducted process mapping workshops with stakeholders in order to prepare the audit in October. The goal was to create a Business Model in which processes and procedures are interconnected.
- Analysed AS9100D requirements;
- Determined processes, inputs, outputs and procedures with stakeholders;
- Animated workshops;
- Created a Business Model;
- Participated in the construction, design and deployment of the model (Visio).

Skills: Communication, Team work, Analytical mind, Process Thinker, Project Management, Flexible, Adaptable, Visio
